1. Arthur Hayes: Bitcoin is expected to rise to $1 million by 2028, but there may be tactical short-selling opportunities in the short term;
2. Ministry of Commerce: China urges the United States to stop the 232 tariff measures as soon as possible;
3. Wall Street big short: shorting Strategy and buying Bitcoin;
4. The whales who previously shorted BTC, ETH and SOL have made a profit of $2.17 million on BTC and $1.77 million on SOL;
5. Kamino's third quarter short-investment qualification check channel has been launched, and 26 million US dollars of KMNO will be distributed to users in May;
6. Trump: The United States is negotiating with Iran on long-term peace, and Iran has roughly agreed to the terms of the agreement;
7. Binance Financial Management, one-click coin purchase, flash exchange, and leveraged Nexpace (NXPC) are launched;
8. Bitget has launched U-based NXPC perpetual contracts with a leverage range of 1-50 times;
9. A certain address has now made a floating profit of more than $2.4 million in NXPC transactions, with a return rate of 135%;
10. An Ethereum ICO participant's address deposited 2,839 ETH to Kraken;
11. Deutsche Bank: The Fed may not cut interest rates until December;
12. The Singapore court approved Sonic Labs' application to liquidate the Multichain Foundation;
13. Loopscale: Law enforcement agencies assisted in identifying the mastermind behind the vulnerability attack, and the investigation of the incident has ended;
14. Binance Alpha launched NXPC;
15. Binance announced the participation threshold for the NXPC airdrop, 187 points are required to participate.
